docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_portable_core_baseline_inventory.log:7865:docs/strategy/V0.4_PROFESSIONAL_SINGLE_USER_STRATEGY.md:212:The next strategic step is therefore not Pattern Advisor expansion and not broader release automation. The next step is a thin local Tkinter cockpit over the existing safe action layer, with visible status, command output, latest command report, latest terminal log, clean-state checks, and gate buttons. Shell-to-Python portability remains part of this direction: GUI and CLI adapters should call explicit Python-backed helpers or argument-vector actions, not synthesize fragile shell snippets.
